{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sitting across from Cypher is Agent Smith.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT SMITH
{DIALOGUE}: Do we have a deal, Mr. Reagan?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cypher chews the steak loudly, smacking it between his teeth.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CYPHER
{DIALOGUE}: Mmm, so, so fucking good.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Smith watches him shovel another hunk of meat into his mouth.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CYPHER
{DIALOGUE}: You know, I know that this steak doesn't exist.
{DIALOGUE}: I know when I put it in my mouth, the Matrix is telling my brain that it is juicy and delicious.
{DIALOGUE}: After nine years, do you know what I've realized?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pausing, he examines the meat skewered on his fork.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pops it in, eyes rolling up, savoring the tender beef melting in his mouth.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CYPHER
{DIALOGUE}: Ignorance is bliss.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT SMITH
{DIALOGUE}: Then we have a deal?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CYPHER
{DIALOGUE}: I don't want to remember nothing.
{DIALOGUE}: Nothing!
{DIALOGUE}: You understand?
