{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MAIN DECK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Trinity's eyes open, a sense of relief surging through her at the sight of the ship.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Tank unplugs her, she sees his charred wounds.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TRINITY
{DIALOGUE}: Tank, you're hurt.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TANK
{DIALOGUE}: I'll be all right.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TRINITY
{DIALOGUE}: Dozer?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tank's face tightens.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TRINITY
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry, Tank.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NIKO HOTEL (MATRIX) - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A Japanese luxury hotel in downtown Chicago.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A military helicopter sets down on the roof.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Heavily armed Marines begin to deploy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Agent Jones gets out of the helicopter, flanked by columns of Marines.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They open the roof access door and enter the top-floor maintenance level of the hotel.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. TOP FLOOR (MATRIX) - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They get in the elevator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At every door, at least two Marines stop and post guard.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HALL (MATRIX) - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They exit the elevator and walk to the Presidential suite; the final two Marines post guard.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. PRESIDENTIAL SUITE (MATRIX) - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Inside, he finds Agent Smith.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT JONES
{DIALOGUE}: There is a problem.
{DIALOGUE}: Reagan has failed to secure the hardware.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Agent Smith stares out the window.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT SMITH
{DIALOGUE}: Never send a human to do a machine's job.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT JONES
{DIALOGUE}: But if Reagan has failed, why haven't they pulled the plug?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT SMITH
{DIALOGUE}: Haven't you learned by now, that it is impossible to understand why they do the things they do?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT SMITH
{DIALOGUE}: Continue as planned.
{DIALOGUE}: Trace his signal to locate their position and deploy an extermination unit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Morpheus is handcuffed to a chair, stripped to the waist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is bleeding from numerous wounds and is pumped full of serum, alternately shivering and sweating.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is hooked up to various monitors with white disk electrodes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Agent Brown begins running a trace program.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MAIN DECK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Neo looks at Morpheus whose body is covered with a cold sweat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NEO
{DIALOGUE}: What are they doing to him?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TANK
{DIALOGUE}: They're cracking his mind.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NEO
{DIALOGUE}: How?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TANK
{DIALOGUE}: They inject virus-like serums to break down the system.
{DIALOGUE}: It's like cracking a computer.
{DIALOGUE}: All it takes is time.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NEO
{DIALOGUE}: How much time?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TANK
{DIALOGUE}: Depends on the mind.
{DIALOGUE}: But eventually, it will crack and his alpha pattern will change from this to this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tank punches several commands on Morpheus' personal unit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The monitor waves change from a chaotic pattern to an orderly symmetrical one.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TANK
{DIALOGUE}: When it does, Morpheus will tell them anything they want to know.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NEO
{DIALOGUE}: The access codes to Zion.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TANK
