{CHARACTER_NAME}: TANK
{DIALOGUE}: You saw that place.
{DIALOGUE}: It's suicide.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She glares at him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TANK
{DIALOGUE}: I know what Morpheus means to you --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TRINITY
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: No, I don't think you do.
{DIALOGUE}: If you did, then you would know that I'm not letting him go.
{DIALOGUE}: Not without a fight, Tank.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She yanks her harness tight.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TRINITY
{DIALOGUE}: Not without a fight.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. PRESIDENTIAL SUITE (MATRIX) - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Agent Smith stands in the bedroon of the enormous suite, staring out the windows at the city, below, shimmering with brilliant sunlight.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT SMITH
{DIALOGUE}: Have you ever stood and stared at it, Morpheus?
{DIALOGUE}: Marveled at its beauty.
{DIALOGUE}: Its genius.
{DIALOGUE}: Billions of people just living out their lives... oblivious.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Agent Brown sucks a serum from a glass vial, filling a hypodermic needle.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT SMITH
{DIALOGUE}: Did you know that the first Matrix was designed to be a perfect human world?
{DIALOGUE}: Where none suffered, where everyone would be happy.
{DIALOGUE}: It was a disaster.
{DIALOGUE}: No one would accept the program.
{DIALOGUE}: Entire crops were lost.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Agent Brown jams the needle into Morpheus' shoulder, and plunges down.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT SMITH
{DIALOGUE}: Some believed we lacked the programming language to describe your perfect world.
{DIALOGUE}: But I believe that, as a species, human beings define their reality through suffering and misery.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Agent Brown studies the screens as the life signs react violently to the injection.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT SMITH
{DIALOGUE}: The perfect world was a dream that your primitive cerebrum kept trying to wake up from.
{DIALOGUE}: Which is why the Matrix was re-designed to this: the peak of your civilization.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns from the window.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT SMITH
{DIALOGUE}: I say 'your civilization' because as soon as we start thinking for you, it really becomes our civilization, which is, of course, what this is all about.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sits down directly in front of Morpheus.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT SMITH
{DIALOGUE}: Evolution, Morpheus.
{DIALOGUE}: Evolution.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He lifts Morpheus' head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT SMITH
{DIALOGUE}: Like the dinosaur.
{DIALOGUE}: Look out that window.
{DIALOGUE}: You had your time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Morpheus stares hard at him, trying hard not to show the pain racking his mind.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT SMITH
{DIALOGUE}: The future is our world, Morpheus.
{DIALOGUE}: The future is our time.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MAIN DECK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Neo goes to his chair and begins strapping in.
