{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. PRESIDENTIAL SUITE (MATRIX) - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Agent Smith sits casually across from Morpheus who is hunched over, his body leaking and twitching.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT SMITH
{DIALOGUE}: I'd like to share a revelation that I've had during my time here.
{DIALOGUE}: It came to me when I tried to classify your species.
{DIALOGUE}: I've realized that you are not actually mammals.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The life signs continue their chaotic patterns.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT SMITH
{DIALOGUE}: Every mammal on this planet instinctively develops a natural equilibrium with the surrounding environment.
{DIALOGUE}: But you humans do not.
{DIALOGUE}: You move to an area and you multiply and multiply until every natural resource is consumed and the only way you can survive is to spread to another area.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He leans forward.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT SMITH
